Ivory Coast Cocoa-Beans Exports From Abidjan Port Soar in June

-- B y   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 
2011-07-26T16:30:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/ivory-coast-cocoa-beans-exports-from-abidjan-port-soar-in-june.html
Exports of  cocoa beans  from  Ivory
Coast ’s port of Abidjan soared in June, according to statistics
from the harbor.  Shipments rose to 114,672 metric tons in June from 5,650
tons in the same period a year earlier, the data showed. Exports
of cocoa products increased 32 percent to 25,435 tons.  Ivory Coast, the world’s biggest cocoa producer, harvests
its main crop from October through March while a mid, or light,
crop is collected from April through September.  The following is a breakdown of cocoa-product exports from
the port of Abidjan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Olivier Monnier in Abidjan via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 